# FastAPI Backend Deployment on AWS EC2 (Ubuntu)

This guide explains how to deploy a FastAPI backend on an Ubuntu EC2 instance using:

* FastAPI
* Uvicorn
* Systemd Service
* Nginx Reverse Proxy
* GitHub Repository

---

## Prerequisites

* AWS EC2 Ubuntu instance
* SSH key pair (`.pem`)
* Security Group allowing:

  * SSH (22)
  * HTTP (80)
  * HTTPS (443) *(optional)*

---

## 1. Connect to EC2 Instance

```bash
ssh -i "My First Key Pair.pem" ubuntu@<EC2_PUBLIC_DNS>
```

Example:

```bash
ssh -i "My First Key Pair.pem" ubuntu@ec2-xx-xx-xx-xx.compute-1.amazonaws.com
```

---

## 2. Update Server Packages

```bash
sudo apt update
sudo apt upgrade -y
```

---

## 3. Install Required Dependencies

### Python

```bash
sudo apt install python3-pip python3-venv python3-dev -y
```

### Nginx

```bash
sudo apt install nginx -y
```

### Git

```bash
sudo apt install git -y
```

---

## 4. Clone Backend Repository

```bash
cd ~

git clone https://github.com/<username>/<repository>.git

cd <repository>
```

Example:

```bash
git clone https://github.com/manikantakallakuri8-bit/backpack-be.git

cd backpack-be
```

---

## 5. Create Virtual Environment

```bash
python3 -m venv venv
```

Activate the environment:

```bash
source venv/bin/activate
```

---

## 6. Install Python Dependencies

```bash
pip install -r requirements.txt
```

---

## 7. Configure Environment Variables

Create or edit the `.env` file:

```bash
nano .env
```

Example:

```env
DATABASE_URL=your_database_url
SECRET_KEY=your_secret_key
OPENAI_API_KEY=your_api_key
```

Save and exit.

---

## 8. Create Systemd Service

Create a service file:

```bash
sudo nano /etc/systemd/system/backpack.service
```

Paste:

```ini
[Unit]
Description=Backpack FastAPI Application
After=network.target

[Service]
User=ubuntu
WorkingDirectory=/home/ubuntu/backpack-be
Environment="PATH=/home/ubuntu/backpack-be/venv/bin"
EnvironmentFile=/home/ubuntu/backpack-be/.env

ExecStart=/home/ubuntu/backpack-be/venv/bin/uvicorn main:app \
    --host 0.0.0.0 \
    --port 8000

Restart=always
RestartSec=3

[Install]
WantedBy=multi-user.target
```

> Note: Replace `backpack-be` with your project directory if different.

---

## 9. Enable and Start Service

Reload systemd:

```bash
sudo systemctl daemon-reload
```

Enable service on boot:

```bash
sudo systemctl enable backpack
```

Start service:

```bash
sudo systemctl start backpack
```

Check status:

```bash
sudo systemctl status backpack
```

---

## 10. Configure Nginx Reverse Proxy

Create an Nginx site configuration:

```bash
sudo nano /etc/nginx/sites-available/backpack
```

Paste:

```nginx
server {
    listen 80;
    server_name _; #replace _ with domain name like backpackapp.duckdns.org

    location / {
        proxy_pass http://127.0.0.1:8000;

        proxy_set_header Host $host;
        proxy_set_header X-Real-IP $remote_addr;
        proxy_set_header X-Forwarded-For $proxy_add_x_forwarded_for;
        proxy_set_header X-Forwarded-Proto $scheme;
    }
}
```

---

## 11. Enable Nginx Configuration

```bash
sudo ln -s /etc/nginx/sites-available/backpack /etc/nginx/sites-enabled/
```

Remove default configuration:

```bash
sudo rm /etc/nginx/sites-enabled/default
```

---

## 12. Test and Restart Nginx

Validate configuration:

```bash
sudo nginx -t
```

Restart Nginx:

```bash
sudo systemctl restart nginx
```

Check status:

```bash
sudo systemctl status nginx
```

Install Certbot
```bash
sudo apt install certbot python3-certbot-nginx -y
```

Run Certbot:
```bash
sudo certbot --nginx -d backpackapi.duckdns.org
```
---

## 13. Monitor Logs

### FastAPI Service Logs

```bash
sudo journalctl -u backpack -f
```

### Nginx Logs

```bash
sudo tail -f /var/log/nginx/error.log
```

```bash
sudo tail -f /var/log/nginx/access.log
```

---

## 14. Common Commands

### Restart Backend

```bash
sudo systemctl restart backpack
```

### Stop Backend

```bash
sudo systemctl stop backpack
```

### Start Backend

```bash
sudo systemctl start backpack
```

### View Service Status

```bash
sudo systemctl status backpack
```

### Reload Nginx

```bash
sudo systemctl reload nginx
```

---

## 15. Deploy Updates

Pull latest code:

```bash
cd ~/backpack-be

git pull origin main
```

Activate virtual environment:

```bash
source venv/bin/activate
```

Install new dependencies (if any):

```bash
pip install -r requirements.txt
```

Restart application:

```bash
sudo systemctl restart backpack
```

---

## Optional: HTTPS with Let's Encrypt

Install Certbot:

```bash
sudo apt install certbot python3-certbot-nginx -y
```

Generate SSL certificate:

```bash
sudo certbot --nginx -d yourdomain.com
```

Auto-renewal test:

```bash
sudo certbot renew --dry-run
```

